<br>
&quot;Kate - do Muslims have an end time/ judgement day belief?&quot;<br>
<br>
Yes, Judgment Day/End Times are quite central to our faith.  However, it is stated explicity in the Qur'an and in the Hadiths that people would ask Prophet Muhammad when Judgment Day would be and he always replied &quot;only God knows&quot; (paraphrasing).  There is a lot of info on &quot;Signs of the End of Time&quot;, and there are &quot;major&quot; signs and &quot;lesser&quot; signs, mostly transmitted through ahadith, but it's sketchy, and people debate as to what they really mean, are they literal or figurative, etc.  The vast majority agree that it is not really productive to get into that overly much.  It's like debating about when you're going to die, will it be tomorrow or will it be in 50 years, who knows?  And what is the point really, since you should be focusing on how you lead your life, not when it will end.. JMO<br>
<br>
HTH<br>
<br>
Kate<br>
