<br>
But I am wondering, why all the elaberate prophey in each? Is it because they are so vague and can really be made to fit almost every era that it scares people into behaving correcting?&quot;<br>
<br>
I don't find it strange at all.  Many people ponder on such issues.. how did it all begin, how will it all end, what is our purpose here, etc.  I think it's pretty common, I just personally don't find it productive to dwell on the end part too much.  I mean, it's important as a Muslim to believe that there will be a Judgment Day, but it is more important to realize you could fall down and die from a heart attack in the next 5 minutes, so you should live your life with the idea that it won't last forever.  Meaning, don't spend your time living an &quot;inappropriate&quot; life counting on having enough time at the end to &quot;go straight&quot;.  We believe that once you die, you're done and just wait around until Judgment Day.. you can't better or worsen your position once you die, that's it.  So really, what we should be more concerned about is when we are going to die.. we don't believe that anything we do can accelerate or delay the coming of the Last Day, it will happen regardless, so to really try and study all the signs and try and work towards achieving them (that sounds really strange to me) or preventing them, that would be a waste of time.<br>
<br>
JMO<br>
<br>
Kate <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9fb7df><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mightyk>MightyK</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 229<br> <font color=#3333ff>(4/21/03 7:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: End Times</span><hr size=1> Kate (and others) - why the need for the propheys in the first place then? Why were they put in your holy books? <br>
