<br>
Do you mean, since we can't effect any change why do we need to know about it?  Once again, speaking for myself here personally, when I read the writings about the End of Time it is simply a reminder to me that all life comes to an end.. I mean, we also know that one day our sun will collapse (somebody science-minded help me out here), and I imagine there are those who are interested to learn about the stages leading up to that event.. why?  Do they hope to be able to prevent it?  I don't think so, I think it's just part of our human need to know.<br>
<br>
As far as learning about Judgment Day, I think that is different.  Learning about the End of Time, the signs leading up to that, etc., I think is done out of curiosity; but learning about the Day of Judgement, it encourages, inspires you to be prepared for it.  I've listened to various lectures on these topics in the Islamic viewpoint, and there's a difference between when they talk about End Times, and when they talk about the Day of Judgement.<br>
<br>
Kate <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9fb7df><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> sweetpeas mommy</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#3333ff>(4/21/03 1:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   why all the concern?</span><hr size=1> Kim, I think this is just part of human nature. There are lots of things that I can't control and that don't really affect my life overmuch that I am interested in. Think about the news as an example...how many news stories really affect us? Obviously, a lot do but a lot have nothing to do with me and yet I am interested in them anyway.<br>
<br>
From my perspective too, there is a healthy level of interest and then there is I'm-so-obsessed-I-eat-sleep-and-drink-this level of interest in the endtimes, you know? I think in its healthiest sense from a Christian mindset, the endtimes can be taken as a reminder to live your life to its fullest and to the best of your ability because you might not have tomorrow. <br>
<br>
Anyway, don't know if that makes sense, but that's my take.<br>
