<br>
I have read a lot on this, and I think it is very possible that the early Christians did not worship Jesus as divine.  A lot of theologians believe that Jesus never claimed to be God and that his message was corrupted by later followers, such as Paul.  As far as Christian groups today, I don't know of any that specifically teach that Jesus is not divine, though there are certainly individuals who have their doubts and I have friends who joined a Universalist Unitarian Church for that reason.  <br>
<br>
